This paper is about image-to-image translation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves using a new loss function based on information theory, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on various real-world datasets, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and potentially neural networks (cs.NE) as well.
